  "title": "Beam Be Gone",
  "description": "Turns the beacon beam invisible when passing through tinted glass",
  "body": "\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\n  <center>\n<img src=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=view&id=1UkW4Q4VTXbp-Ro0eQAX0__k9ZhSEIZkC\"  alt=\"Beam Be Gone Logo\">\n<h2>\n<b>A simple mod that turns the beacon beam invisible when passing through tinted glass</b>\n</h2>\n<br>\n<a href=\"\">\n<img alt=\"modrinth\" height=\"56\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/cozy/available/modrinth_vector.svg\">\n</a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/Ramixin/BeamBeGone\">\n<img alt=\"github\" height=\"56\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/cozy/available/github_vector.svg\">\n</a>\n<br>\n<img alt=\"fabric\" height=\"40\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/compact/supported/fabric_vector.svg\">\n<img alt=\"forge\" height=\"40\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/compact/unsupported/forge_vector.svg\">\n</center>\n</div>\n\n## What if I want other blocks to do the same?\n\n---\nFirstly, make sure you are using version 0.0.2 or newer. To add a new block, simply add it to the tag `bbg:makes_beam_invisible`. It's that easy!\n\n## License\n\n---\nThis project is under an MIT license",
